es_Guy_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 436, \"end\": 441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9996975125164465, \"rank\": 0.00030257507383161223, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 348}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic title\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They showed it was no fluke by being crowned world champions in the event last year and, although they were outside the medals at this year's Worlds, Richards was the only member of the first-choice quartet in action.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 677, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no fluke\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"world champions\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 520}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's Worlds\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"the only member\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"the first-choice quartet\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richards, like Adam Peaty,missed out on an individual gold in the individual event over 200m by just two hundredths of a secondto David Popovici on Monday while teammate Duncan Scott was agonisingly denied a medal by a few hundredths of a second.\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Popovici\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Popovici\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9913273362707572, \"rank\": 0.004373974849644039, \"text\": \"Duncan Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual gold\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 737}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual event\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"200m\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"just two hundredths\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"a secondto\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 833}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"a few hundredths\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 912}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 924}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Richards insisted that missed opportunity had only inspired him further to go for gold.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1018, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"missed opportunity\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's something that I have dreamt of since I was a little boy,\\\" said the 21-year-old Welshman in the aftermath of his first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\", \"score\": 0.9726134421819075, \"rank\": 0.028157692052034413, \"text\": \"Welshman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1035}, {\"ngram\": \"a little boy\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1082}, {\"ngram\": \"the aftermath\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"his first Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1158}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd be lying if I said I wasn't dreaming of being one step higher on the podium.\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But my week's not done, it's made me hungrier than ever.\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my week\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Myself and Duncan, second and fourth, gutted for him by the way just missing out on the medal, he deserves it more than anyone but that bodes well for our 4x200m.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1312, \"end\": 1318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Duncan\", \"score\": 0.9999973226394475, \"rank\": 2.677366833064187e-06, \"text\": \"Duncan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Duncan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Duncan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1364}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"our 4x200m.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1463}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If fuels me on for the rest of this week.\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"this week\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If anything, it has added more fire to my belly.\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more fire\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"my belly\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have got a lot more to come this week.\\\"\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1596, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was agony for Scott, who was just fractions outside a medal in the same race which would have matched Sir Chris Hoy's record of seven Olympic medals for Team GB.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1618, \"end\": 1623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Steiner\", \"score\": 0.9741712909399539, \"rank\": 0.02651351891047588, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Steiner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Steiner\"}, {\"begin\": 1710, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 1757, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 1.3403078706560483e-13, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"agony\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1613}, {\"ngram\": \"fractions\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"the same race\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"seven Olympic medals\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as Hoy's medal record the British team, Scott is also bidding for a first individual Olympic title at the age of 27 and has another shot later in the Games in the 200m individual medley.\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8738717319187755, \"rank\": 0.1430285193535199, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1815, \"end\": 1820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Steiner\", \"score\": 0.9741712909399539, \"rank\": 0.02651351891047588, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Steiner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Steiner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a first individual Olympic title\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"another shot\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m individual medley\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions Discover a hidden island paradise in the Indian Ocean After finishing fourth last night, he said: \\\"I do not really know what to say.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2094, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Proud\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"Enhanced Games Sports quiz\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2041}, {\"ngram\": \"100 hard questions\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredible year\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"Grand Slam Track decision\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"2025 ambitions\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2161}, {\"ngram\": \"a hidden island paradise\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2195}, {\"ngram\": \"the Indian Ocean\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2215}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fourth is a horrible place to come.\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2334, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a horrible place\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several hundredths of a second away from winning a medal, or even better.\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Several hundredths\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was buzzing going into that and had really good fun in there.\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"really good fun\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking back, I maybe should have pushed it on a bit earlier.\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2536, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was really tight and came down to the finish but I did not quite have it today.\\\"\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Richards, with a newly done tattoo of the Olympic rings on his right hand, his build-up has been in stark contrast to Tokyo where he won as a teenager.\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9996975125164465, \"rank\": 0.00030257507383161223, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Richards\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2634}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2681}, {\"ngram\": \"his right hand\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"his build-up\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2713}, {\"ngram\": \"stark contrast\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"a teenager\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Covid lockdown, his parents bought a pop-up pool for the family garden and he effectively attached a bungee cord to a garage door to enable him to do intensity training when pools were shut down.\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Covid lockdown\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"his parents\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2813}, {\"ngram\": \"a pop-up pool\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"the family garden\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2856}, {\"ngram\": \"a bungee cord\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2898}, {\"ngram\": \"a garage door\", \"from\": 2902, \"to\": 2915}, {\"ngram\": \"intensity training\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2954}, {\"ngram\": \"pools\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He looks destined to be the superstar of Team GB's swimming set-up in the future and does not lack for confidence, saying he wanted to be, \\\"one of the greatest or the greatest\\\".\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 3160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3024, \"end\": 3031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 1.3403078706560483e-13, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the superstar\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3020}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3063}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He suggested the British team might be cursed by two hundredths of a second having lost by the same fingertip finish to Peaty.\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3179, \"end\": 3186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8738717319187755, \"rank\": 0.1430285193535199, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two hundredths\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3225}, {\"ngram\": \"the same fingertip\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3271}, {\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not be too disappointed with that,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's my first ever individual medal at an Olympic Games so to walk away from that with a silver medal is fantastic.\", \"from\": 3342, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my first ever individual medal\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3378}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3398}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Obviously, two hundredths off gold is excruciatingly frustrating.\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3526, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3491, \"to\": 3495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It felt as if I had touched the wall first.\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought I'd got it but you know it wasn't my best finish.\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3630, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my best finish\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I'd be lying if I said it was fantastic.\", \"from\":